---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { GITHUB_URL, RELEASE_URL } from "../../consts";

const title = "Sketch flowcharts and mind maps without leaving your notes";
const description = "Diagramming usually means switching to a separate app and losing your train of thought. inkwell's built-in Canvas keeps drawing one keystroke away from writing.";
const datePublished = "2026-07-13";
const dateModified = "2026-07-13";

const blogPostingSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  headline: title,
  description,
  datePublished,
  dateModified,
  url: "https://inkwell-lp.vercel.app/blog/canvas-sketch-ideas-in-your-notes",
  author: { "@id": "https://inkwell-lp.vercel.app/#organization" },
  publisher: { "@id": "https://inkwell-lp.vercel.app/#organization" },
  mainEntityOfPage: "https://inkwell-lp.vercel.app/blog/canvas-sketch-ideas-in-your-notes",
};
---

<Layout title={`inkwell — ${title}`} description={description}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(blogPostingSchema)} />

  <!-- ── Nav ── -->
  <nav>
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="wordmark">
        <img src="/inkwell-icon.svg" alt="inkwell" width="26" height="26" />
        inkwell
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/#features">Features</a>
        <a href="/#canvas">Canvas</a>
        <a href="/#themes">Themes</a>
        <a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
        <a href="/blog" class="nav-active">Blog</a>
      </div>
      <a href={RELEASE_URL} class="btn-nav" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- ── Content ── -->
  <main class="post-content">
    <a href="/blog" class="back-link">← Blog</a>
    <div class="section-label">July 13, 2026 · 4 min read</div>
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Some ideas aren't sentences. A system architecture, a decision tree, a
      quick sketch of how three pieces of a project connect — text can
      describe them, but a diagram shows them instantly. The usual cost of
      drawing one is a context switch: open Excalidraw, open Miro, find the
      right board, come back, paste a screenshot. inkwell skips that
      entirely by putting a full drawing canvas next to the editor.
    </p>

    <h2>One shortcut away from a blank canvas</h2>
    <p>
      Click the <strong>Draw</strong> icon in the sidebar and a canvas opens
      alongside your vault — shared across every note, not tied to a single
      document. It saves automatically to{" "}
      <code>.inkwell/canvas.json</code>, so there's no export step and
      nothing to remember to save before you close the app.
    </p>

    <h2>A toolset built for diagrams, not general illustration</h2>
    <p>
      The tool set is deliberately narrow: select, pen, rectangle, ellipse,
      line, arrow, and text, each bound to a single letter key (<kbd>V</kbd>,{" "}
      <kbd>P</kbd>, <kbd>R</kbd>, <kbd>E</kbd>, <kbd>L</kbd>, <kbd>A</kbd>,{" "}
      <kbd>T</kbd>). Hold <kbd>⇧</kbd> while drawing to constrain a rectangle
      to a square or snap a line to 45°. It's fast precisely because it
      isn't trying to be a full illustration app — it's trying to be the
      fastest way to turn "let me draw this" into a diagram.
    </p>

    <h2>Six templates for the diagrams you draw most</h2>
    <p>
      Most technical diagrams fall into a handful of shapes, so inkwell
      ships six ready-made templates that load pre-arranged and fit
      themselves to the viewport automatically:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flowchart</strong> — Start, two steps, and End with arrows.</li>
      <li><strong>Mind Map</strong> — a central topic with six branches.</li>
      <li><strong>Org Chart</strong> — a lead with two managers and three reports.</li>
      <li><strong>Sequence Diagram</strong> — two actors with request / response / callback arrows.</li>
      <li><strong>Timeline</strong> — four milestones on a horizontal axis.</li>
      <li><strong>Venn Diagram</strong> — two overlapping labelled sets.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Load one, relabel the boxes, and you have a working diagram in under a
      minute instead of building the layout from scratch.
    </p>

    <h2>Notes and drawing, side by side</h2>
    <p>
      Press <kbd>⌘/</kbd> or click the note icon in the top-right of the
      canvas to slide in a markdown notes panel at half the canvas width.
      The canvas stays fully interactive while it's open, so you can jot
      down the reasoning behind a diagram — why this box connects to that
      one — without switching away from either. Those notes save separately
      to <code>.inkwell/canvas-notes.md</code>, still just another plain
      text file in your vault.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Why this matters more than it sounds:</strong> the friction of
      switching apps is often the reason a diagram never gets drawn at all.
      Removing that friction doesn't just make diagramming faster — it
      changes whether it happens.
    </div>

    <p class="post-cta-text">
      Full tool reference, shape styling options, and keyboard shortcuts are
      in the <a href="/docs#canvas">Canvas docs</a>.
    </p>
  </main>

  <!-- ── Footer ── -->
  <footer>
    <div class="footer-inner">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <img src="/inkwell-icon.svg" alt="inkwell" width="20" height="20" />
        <span>inkwell</span>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-copy">
        An open-source project by <a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">coros-hq</a>. Built with Tauri, React, and Rust.
      </p>
      <a href="/privacy" class="footer-docs">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/docs" class="footer-docs">Docs</a>
      <a href="/blog" class="footer-docs">Blog</a>
      <a href={GITHUB_URL} class="footer-gh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="GitHub">
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.3 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.6.113.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23A11.509 11.509 0 0 1 12 5.803c1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576C20.566 21.797 24 17.3 24 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
        GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Nav (shared pattern) ── */
  nav {
    position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 50; backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    background: var(--nav-bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .nav-inner {
    max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 14px 32px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 32px;
  }
  .wordmark { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; font-weight: 500; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .wordmark img { border-radius: 7px; }
  .nav-links { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 24px; flex: 1; }
  .nav-links a { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .nav-active { color: var(--text) !important; font-weight: 500; }
  .btn-nav {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500;
    padding: 7px 14px; border-radius: 8px; background: var(--accent-dim);
    border: 1px solid rgba(196,131,42,0.25); color: var(--accent-light); flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-nav:hover { background: rgba(196,131,42,0.22); border-color: rgba(196,131,42,0.38); }

  /* ── Content ── */
  .post-content { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 56px 32px 96px; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 24px; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .section-label {
    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  h1 { font-size: 34px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 18px; line-height: 1.2; }
  h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text); margin: 40px 0 14px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .lead { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  ul { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.8; padding-left: 22px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  li strong { color: var(--text); }

  code { font-family: "SF Mono","Fira Code",monospace; font-size: 12.5px; background: var(--bg-subtle); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--accent-light); }
  kbd {
    display: inline-block; font-family: "SF Mono",monospace; font-size: 11px;
    background: var(--bg-subtle); border: 1px solid var(--border-mid);
    border-bottom-width: 2px; border-radius: 5px; padding: 1px 6px;
    color: var(--text); line-height: 1.5;
  }
  a { color: var(--accent-light); transition: color 0.12s; }
  a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .post-content p a { text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: rgba(212, 152, 64, 0.4); text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .post-content p a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }

  .callout {
    background: var(--accent-dim); border: 1px solid rgba(196,131,42,0.2);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px 20px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2);
    line-height: 1.7; margin: 24px 0;
  }
  .callout strong { color: var(--accent-light); }

  .post-cta-text { margin-top: 40px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }

  /* ── Footer (shared pattern) ── */
  footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 28px 32px; }
  .footer-inner { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px; }
  .footer-brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-2); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .footer-brand img { border-radius: 5px; }
  .footer-copy { flex: 1; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-3); }
  .footer-copy a { color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: rgba(154, 142, 126, 0.4); text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .footer-copy a:hover { color: var(--text); text-decoration-color: var(--text); }
  .footer-gh { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); transition: color 0.15s; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .footer-gh:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .footer-docs { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); transition: color 0.15s; flex-shrink: 0; margin-right: 8px; }
  .footer-docs:hover { color: var(--text); }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .nav-links { display: none; }
    .post-content { padding: 40px 20px 72px; }
    h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    footer { padding: 28px 20px; }
    .footer-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px; }
  }
</style>
